The course gives an overview of the main periods of Italian literary history from the 13th Century till present day and the main authors of Italian literary history will be introduced. The selected authors and literary works will be discussed in more detail during the course, including introducing some films based on literary works.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an overview of the main periods and phenomena of Italian literary history.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student On completion of the course the students know the most important phenomena, authors and works of Italian literature. The students have read some important literary works (in Estonian translation) and are able to associate them with historic and cultural context.
